# Audio gain normalization



Victory and intro clips use per-file gains in `app/generated/audio-gain-map.js` (target -16 LUFS). Unmapped clips play at default volume and sound jarring.



Win clip rosters are auto-generated in `win-clips-manifest.js` from files in `audio/win/<category>/`.



UI clip paths live in `scripts/audio-paths.mjs` and are emitted to `audio-paths.js`.



Gain analysis is incremental: only new or changed files are re-analyzed (cached in `.cache/audio-gain-cache.json`). Use `--full` for a complete rescan.



## When this applies



After any change that adds, removes, or renames clips:



- Files under `audio/win/<category>/` or `audio/ui/`

- Paths in `scripts/audio-paths.mjs`



## Required follow-up (same task)



1. Run `npm run refresh-audio`, double-click `scripts/shortcuts/Refresh Audio.bat`, or use `scripts/shortcuts/Watch Audio.bat` during an editing session

2. Confirm `win-clips-manifest.js` lists the new clip under the correct category

3. Confirm `app/generated/audio-gain-map.js` was regenerated and includes the new paths

4. Mention in your summary that gains were re-scanned



Do not skip this step unless the user explicitly asks to skip normalization.



## Adding a win clip



1. Drop `.mp3` or `.wav` into the category folder (see `scripts/win-clip-categories.mjs`)

2. Refresh audio (see below)

3. Prefix filenames with `_` to exclude drafts from the roster



Drafts can also live in `audio/_staging/` (excluded from gain analysis and the victory roster).



## Refresh options



- **Watch mode (best for sporadic adds):** double-click `scripts/shortcuts/Watch Audio.bat` or run `npm run watch-audio`, then reload the browser after updates

- **One-shot refresh:** double-click `scripts/shortcuts/Refresh Audio.bat` or run `npm run refresh-audio`

- **Full rescan (rare):** `npm run analyze-audio-gains -- --full`



## Playback reference



`getNormalizedVolume()` in `app/main.js` resolves paths and looks up `window.audioGainMap`.
